sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Q as Discovery question
    participant Tool as Tool-class screen
    participant Prov as Provenance and legality check
    participant Exposure as Identity-exposure check
    participant Repro as Reproducibility check
    participant Mini as Corroboration and minimization review
    participant Privacy as Privacy-drift check
    participant Review as Reviewer approval
    participant Matrix as Provenance matrix
    Q->>Tool: Describe public-source task and allowed data boundary
    Tool->>Prov: Record source origin and legal basis
    Tool->>Exposure: Check rate limits, account exposure, and identity risk
    Tool->>Repro: Preserve reproducible query and retrieval notes
    Prov->>Mini: Forward only reviewable source material
    Exposure->>Mini: Block if identity exposure exceeds the classroom boundary
    Repro->>Mini: Block if result cannot be reproduced or explained
    Mini->>Privacy: Submit minimized corroborated packet
    Privacy->>Review: Add privacy-drift finding and caveat
    Review->>Matrix: Approve documented provenance and minimization matrix
    Review-->>Q: Otherwise issue blocked-use note and stop
